QA report:
  BUG-01 (P0) Stock Sheet crashes with React Error #31 on every ticker
              run, args=[object with keys {direction, magnitude}]
  BUG-02 (P0) Re-rating shows 0 candidates because universe is hardcoded
              to portfolio+watchlist (both empty for most users)

BUG-01 FIX
  Root: /market/quotes returns price/change_pct as {direction, magnitude}
  for some tickers (the API's signed-numeric convention).  Number(obj)
  becomes NaN safely BUT React still throws if the value reaches JSX.
  +Added safeScalar(v) helper that handles number / string / {direction,
   magnitude} / {value} shapes and returns a signed number or null
  +Defensively unwrapped quote.price + quote.change_pct in the header
  +Added StockSheetErrorBoundary class component wrapping the body so
   a malformed payload anywhere in the sheet shows an inline error
   instead of crashing the whole page.  Reset button restores normal flow.

BUG-02 FIX (3 sub-fixes A/B/C)
  A. Universe selector dropdown: Auto / Multibagger Upload / Portfolio /
     Watchlist / NSE500 / Custom CSV
  B. Multibagger bridge — readMultibaggerSymbols() reads mb3_symbols
     localStorage key.  AUTO mode prefers Multibagger if non-empty.
  C. Model-shift regex expanded for Indian context.
     Was: only US SaaS terms (recurring / ARR / NRR / land-and-expand)
     Now also matches: subscription / annuity / retainer / long-term
     contract / order book / AMC / maintenance contract / managed services
     / channel partner / aftermarket / asset-light / licensing / royalty /
     capex-to-opex / gross margin expansion / operating leverage /
     run-rate revenue.  Catches Indian model-shift signals that the
     US-centric regex missed (~90% of Indian cases per QA).

  Universe-source tag rendered next to count: 'multibagger upload (25)'
  / 'portfolio + watchlist (8)' / 'custom (5)' so user knows what
  universe is being scanned.

Type-check clean.
